                                                            "You try to turn the handle, and the latch unlocks with satisfying smoothness, letting you push the door open and step into the apartment without resistance, bringing you into an uncannily vacant house interior. Indeed, the single-room habitation is almost entirely bare, the only piece of furniture consisting of a conspicuous, regal-looking pillar with a letter prominently resting on it.",
                                                            "Cautiously approaching, you move to the imposing piece of marble stonework while staying on the lookout for traps and ambushes... but as nothing happens and you're pretty confident you've been as vigilant as one could be, you deftly snag the letter and unseal it to find that it contains yet another clue written in a now familiar elegant cursive:",
                                                            "{i}From a duel of competing thunders, you have found your way to this place among the stars,\nNow, plunge from the skies, and dive into the winding, crashing seas,\nTurn over the seabed to find its secrets, but beware the alluring merfolks' siren song, for three will lead you astray with both truth and lies,\nOnly one will tell no lies at all, guiding you to the stamp that is your goal.{/i}",
                                                            "Pocketing the note so you can check it later in case you forget its contents, you leave the barren room, finding nothing else of note in the eerily empty premises.",
